parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch release bearing can cause a clicking noise when the clutch is depressed, which can lead to premature wear of the clutch and transmission components, and potentially cause the transmission to slip out of gear, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Clicking noise occurs when the clutch is depressed
whether the vehicle is in motion or parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slippage can cause the vehicle to lose power or roll backwards, leading to accidents or property damage.
symptoms: Transmission slips out of drive into reverse
vehicle rolls backwards
loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning compressor can cause the air conditioning system to malfunction, leading to discomfort and inconvenience for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The air conditioning system does not cool the air
the air conditioning compressor makes unusual noises
the air conditioning compressor fails to turn on
the air conditioning system leaks refrigerant.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear window defroster can reduce visibility while driving, especially in cold or wet weather conditions, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The rear window defroster does not turn on
the rear window defroster does not clear fog or ice from the window
the rear window defroster is slow to clear fog or ice from the window.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel pressure regulator can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to a loss of power, stalling, and backfiring, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle lurches forward
lacks power
backfires
stalls
or hesitates when accelerating
and may have difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension bolts can cause the shaft to detach, leading to vibrations in the front end, which can affect vehicle stability and handling, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Vibration in the front end
loose or detached suspension components
unusual noises from the front suspension
difficulty steering or maintaining control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the right front suspension can cause vibrations, uneven tire wear, and affect vehicle stability and handling, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Vibration in the front end
uneven tire wear
pulling to one side while driving
difficulty steering or maintaining control of the vehicle.
